FG-411 — Cert “Question • Split • Gap” Ladder
	•	⚖️ Core Message: The petition must climb three rungs: Question • Split • Gap.
	•	📖 Lesson Content: Ladder format: QP (≤15 words); Split (table or 2 rows); Gap (your record pin). End with relief menu.
	•	📝 Assignment: Draft a ladder page with one rung per section.
	•	✅ Model Response: “QP: Must courts reach findings? Split: 2d—no, 9th—yes. Gap: ‘Not reached’ (Dkt 18:2). Relief: grant or GVR.”
	•	💡 Reflection Summary: Rungs invite a climb.
	•	🎨 Visual Concept: A three-step ladder with a gavel at the top.

⸻

FG-412 — Cert Amicus Bank Index (Who • Topic • Hash)
	•	⚖️ Core Message: Amicus briefs work better with a shared index.
	•	📖 Lesson Content: Columns: Amicus • Topic • Pages • SHA-256; post as a PDF/CSV; link to petition microsite.
	•	📝 Assignment: Draft a 5-row amicus bank index.
	•	✅ Model Response: “Amicus A—split map—10 pp—SHA-256 …; Amicus B—policy—8 pp—SHA-256 ….”
	•	💡 Reflection Summary: Indexes amplify voices.
	•	🎨 Visual Concept: A grid of briefs with fingerprint icons.

⸻

FG-413 — Cert Appendix Capture Protocol (Each Tab Logged)
	•	⚖️ Core Message: Every tab must prove its source.
	•	📖 Lesson Content: Tab front matter: Doc title • Source • Capture date • SHA-256. Repeat for sealed S-tabs in separate index.
	•	📝 Assignment: Add capture lines to 3 appendix tabs.
	•	✅ Model Response: “Tab 2—Opinion p.12; captured 09/01; SHA-256 ….”
	•	💡 Reflection Summary: Captures anchor trust.
	•	🎨 Visual Concept: A binder tab with a footer stamp.

⸻

FG-414 — Cert Reply “Misfit Grid”
	•	⚖️ Core Message: Show why respondent’s answer doesn’t fit the split.
	•	📖 Lesson Content: Grid: Circuit • Respondent claim • Actual law/pin. Highlight misfit row.
	•	📝 Assignment: Draft a 3-row misfit grid.
	•	✅ Model Response: “2d Cir.—Respondent: no findings required—But: Doe, 2022, requires them.”
	•	💡 Reflection Summary: Misfits beat adjectives.
	•	🎨 Visual Concept: A grid with one row shaded red.

⸻

FG-415 — Cert “Two-Date Clock” Card
	•	⚖️ Core Message: Keep the judgment + rehearing denial visible; they start the 90-day clock.
	•	📖 Lesson Content: Card: Judgment date; Rehearing denial date; Cert due (90d). Add roll-forward note.
	•	📝 Assignment: Draft your two-date card today.
	•	✅ Model Response: “Judgment 09/01; Rehearing denied 09/15; Cert due 12/14.”
	•	💡 Reflection Summary: Dates anchor petitions.
	•	🎨 Visual Concept: A card with two date chips pointing to a due chip.

⸻

FG-416 — Amicus Formatting Note (Fonts • Length • Hash)
	•	⚖️ Core Message: Amici must certify format compliance.
	•	📖 Lesson Content: Certificate: word count; font; spacing; Rule 33 compliance; PDF Title metadata; SHA-256.
	•	📝 Assignment: Draft a formatting certificate for one amicus.
	•	✅ Model Response: “Word count 8,250; 14-pt font; double-spaced; Rule 33; SHA-256 ….”
	•	💡 Reflection Summary: Compliance = credibility.
	•	🎨 Visual Concept: A ruler + hash footer on a PDF tile.

⸻

FG-417 — Cert Pool Memo Skeleton (QP • Split • Facts • Relief)
	•	⚖️ Core Message: Write as if you’re drafting the clerk’s pool memo.
	•	📖 Lesson Content: Skeleton: (1) Question Presented; (2) Split summary; (3) Neutral facts (2 pins); (4) Relief menu. ≤2 pages.
	•	📝 Assignment: Draft a 4-section memo skeleton for your case.
	•	✅ Model Response: “QP: Must courts reach factor findings? Split: 2d v. 9th. Facts: ‘Not reached’ (Dkt 18:2). Relief: grant/GVR/hold.”
	•	💡 Reflection Summary: If you draft the memo, you guide the clerk.
	•	🎨 Visual Concept: A memo page divided into four labeled blocks.

⸻

FG-418 — Cert OA Prep Grid (Q • Std • Pin • Relief)
	•	⚖️ Core Message: Cert OA is still just a grid of four blocks.
	•	📖 Lesson Content: Build card: Question; Standard (one cite); Pin (record gap); Relief (ladder). Fit on palm.
	•	📝 Assignment: Draft your OA prep grid and hash it.
	•	✅ Model Response: “Q: Must courts reach findings? Std: de novo. Pin: ‘Not reached’ (Dkt 18:2). Relief: remand 21d.”
	•	💡 Reflection Summary: OA is the grid, rehearsed.
	•	🎨 Visual Concept: A pocket grid with four labeled squares.

⸻

FG-419 — Cert Release Table (All Docs • All Hashes)
	•	⚖️ Core Message: Publish a release table after filing.
	•	📖 Lesson Content: Table columns: Date • Doc • SHA-256 • Mirrors • Next step. Post to microsite; hash file itself.
	•	📝 Assignment: Build a 5-row release table for your cert filings.
	•	✅ Model Response: “09/01 — Petition (sha …) — Mirrors M-1/M-2 — Next: response 10/01.”
	•	💡 Reflection Summary: Release tables = procedural memory.
	•	🎨 Visual Concept: A grid with rows stamped “hash verified.”

⸻

FG-420 — SCOTUS Closeout Bundle (Petition • Appendix • Amicus Bank)
	•	⚖️ Core Message: End the cert phase with a ZIP + release note.
	•	📖 Lesson Content: Bundle: Petition.pdf • Appendix.pdf • Amicus briefs • CHECKSUMS.txt • ReleaseNote.md; hash; post mirrors.
	•	📝 Assignment: Export your closeout ZIP and write a 120-word release note.
	•	✅ Model Response: “Release v2—Cert bundle posted: Petition (sha …), Appendix (sha …), Amicus (sha …). Mirrors aligned.”
	•	💡 Reflection Summary: Closure is memory made public.
	•	🎨 Visual Concept: A ribboned ZIP folder with three doc icons + fingerprint.
